items.name: MechWiki
items.title: MechWiki
items.desc: BattleTech is the reboot of the original game that was developed in 1984 by FASA. The new turn-based strategy videogame is co-developed by multiple original developers of the franchise including creator Jordan Weisman. He, along with Mitch Gitelman co-founded Hairbrained Schemes, the studio developing the BattleTech reboot. BattleTech was released on April 24, 2018 and is available on Steam. This wiki is a collaborative resource for the Battletech/MechWarrior franchise and is maintained by the contributions of the fans.

items.desc: The Lethal Weapon Wiki is about about the police crusades of Los Angeles Police Detectives Martin Riggs and Roger Murtaugh. Riggs is the one with the crazy personality while Murtaugh is the old guy who wished he had retired from law enforcement sooner. But despite these circumstances, together these two men make one great crime fighting team.

items.name: Athlepedia, The Athletics Wiki
items.title: Athlepedia, The Athletics Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to Athlepedia
items.desc:
This site is about physical fitness and health.

Don't let the term mislead you -- elite, in the case, has a double meaning. We're talking about the pursuit of excellence, not just in fitness but in knowledge. Elite knowledge of fitness, gleaned from these pages, will help you propel yourself to success faster than normal, however, the reality is that wisdom means nothing without application. So we challenge you to go out and play -- get out and turn up the dial. Make it happen.

items.desc: Teletubbies Wiki is a Teletubbies created website which aims to provide its visitors with information on all the different aspects of the hit CBBC Television series, Teletubbies which originally ran from 31 March 1997 - Febuary 2001, 2002 - present on Cbeebies in the UK and lasted for over 365 episodes. This site is to be about Teletubbies only which means that any visitor is free to edit as long as it has to do with Teletubbies.

items.name: Rosenkreuzstilette Wiki
items.title: Rosenkreuzstilette Wiki
items.headline: The Rosenkreuzstilette Wiki is here for all your RKS needs!
items.desc:
This Wikia covers the games in the Rosenkreuzstilette series as well as several fan materials relating to the series. Rosenkreuzstilette is a series of doujin soft games created by the doujin group [erka:es], taking cues from Capcom's Mega Man franchise, with elements from and references to Konami's Castlevania series and many other titles. The series is known for its Mega Man inspired gameplay as well as its primarily female cast and mystical setting.

This wiki is still in its growing stages, so all help is appreciated! Feel free to contribute in anyway you see fit, whether it is as major as adding translations or as minor as fixing typos. Do not worry about making mistakes, as any errors can be corrected quickly.

items.name: Let's Play Wiki
items.title: Let's Play Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Let's Play Wiki
items.desc:
A Let's Play is a series of videos in which the author records the complete gameplay of a video game, while providing commentary in the form of an informal and ideally entertaining chat with the intended audience.

The goal is to provide the easiest gameplay experience, so that the viewer doesn't need to own the game itself, any hardware (or emulator), or even go through the effort of actually playing; while also giving the chance for the author to enhance further the experience by providing expert insight about the game's knowledge, secrets, production, franchise, backstory, etc. or just otherwise by making jokes or witty commentaries.

items.name: Skillet Wiki
items.title: Skillet Wiki
items.headline: Rock out with Skillet
items.desc:
Skillet is a Christian Rock band that was formed in 1996. The band has released eight albums and received two Grammy nominations. Their album Awake has been certified Platinum and debuted on No. 2 on the Billboard 200, with Comatose certified Gold by RIAA. They have sold over 2 million albums in the U.S. alone and are known for a relentless touring schedule, which garnered them a top five ranking in the Hardest Working Bands of 2011 by Songkick.com.

What are you waiting for? Wanna join the thousands of panheads who rock with Skillet?

items.name: Violetta Wiki
items.title: Violetta Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Violetta Wiki!
items.desc: Violetta is a kids-oriented telenovela that first aired on the Disney Channel Latin America on May 14, 2012. The show is a co-production between Disney Channel Latin America, Disney Channel Europe, Disney Channel Middle East, Disney Channel Africa and Argentine production company Pol-ka Producciones. Violetta features a multinational cast, and tells the story of "Violetta", a musically talented teenager who returns to her hometown to "find love", and explore her passion for music. The show is shot entirely in Buenos Aires.

items.headline: Bienvenidos a la wiki de Violetta
items.desc: Violetta, es una telenovela musical transmitida actualmente por el canal televisivo Disney Channel. Fue transmitida por primera vez en Hispanoamérica e Italia el 14 de marzo de 2012. Violetta narra la historia de una adolescente solitaria y muy talentosa que, tras vivir muchos años en el "viejo continente", regresa a Buenos Aires, su ciudad natal. En su nueva vida encontrará verdaderos amigos, hallará el amor, descubrirá su vocación innata y pasión por la música y, a la vez, construirá y enfrentará la magnífica e interesante experiencia de crecer.
